(200, 1, '2019-02-19 14:00:46', '2019-02-19 07:00:46', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The art with an even extent of spread throughout the Betawi cultural area is Rebana (Tambourine), a membrane music instrument, which in various other areas is referred to as âTerbangâ. It was said that Rebana originates from the word âRobannaâ, which means âOur Godâ. This word occurred since normally in the moslem cultural area this music is used to accompany songs breathing the spirit of Islamism, which often mention âRobannaâ. In the long run this music instrument is referred to as rebana, or expressing it with the robana pronunciation, such as in the Kaligono Village.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Almost all types of java rebana are found in the Central Java and East Java areas. Several types are also found in West Java. There are one specific certain village types, namely Soyar Maole, which is only found in Kaligono Village, Kaligesing Sub-District, Purworejo Regency, Central Java.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Robanna Soyar Maole', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'robanna-soyar-maole', '', '', '2019-02-19 16:31:05', '2019-02-19 09:31:05', '', 0, 'http://localhost/PortalDesaWonosari/?p=200', 0, 'post', '', 0),
